  "texts": [
    "They achieve this by incorporating a critic-network that approximates the value function and an actor-network for directly updating the policy.",
    "The critic-network can be utilized in two ways to reduce the gradient variance: by approximating the Q-function Q or by approximating the state-value function V.",
    "When the critic-network approximates the Q-function, the actor-network parameters are updated by considering all possible actions in a given state, as expressed by the following equation:",
    "This concept has spurred the development of advanced algorithms, such as Deep Deterministic Policy Gradient (DDPG) (Lillicrap et al. 2015).",
    "DDPG directly learns a deterministic policy with samples extracted from the experience replay to aim problems with continuous action spaces."
  ]
